GIT - Basics

Git Is A Software, Git-Hub is a Central Repository

In Git We have 3 Phases,

1. WorkSpace
2. Staging/Index
3. Local Repo

Workspace:- Any New Files Creating Or Existing File Modifications are Coming under Workspace Area.

Staging/Index:- Tracking Information and all Coming under This Area, Like When we commit it will automatically pick the data 
from Configurations Like you know

* User Name (Author Name), Email ID As well as What Purpose we are going to Commit these files Info Will get.

Local Repo:- If Anything you want to Push into Central Repository, That Files Should be there in Local Repository
 [Can't Push the Files into Central Repository By Using Workspace Area/Staging area]
